  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Install the package by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr/local \
            --datadir=/usr/local/share/misc &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install &amp;&amp;
mv -v /usr/local/sbin/update-usbids.sh /usr/local/sbin/update-usbids</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
    <title>Configuration</title>

    <para>
      The <filename>usb.ids</filename> data file is constantly being updated. To
      get a current version of this file, run <command>update-usbids</command>
      as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user. This program
      requires  <xref linkend="wget"/> which is used
      to download the most current file, and replace the existing file in
      <filename class="directory">/usr/local/share/misc</filename>.
    </para>

    <para>
      You may wish to add an entry to <systemitem
      class="username">root</systemitem>'s (or any other user who has write
      privilege to <filename class="directory">/usr/local/share/misc</filename>)
      crontab to automatically update the <filename>usb.ids</filename> file
      periodically.
    </para>

  </sect2>

